Comments: GLADES COUNTY EMERGENCY MANAGEMENT REPORTED A TORNADO TOUCHING DOWN IN GLADES COUNTY NEAR THE INTERSECTION OF U.S. 27 AND STATE ROAD 78. NO REPORT OF INJURIES
A STORM DAMAGE SURVEY SHOWED EVIDENCE OF AN EF-1 TORNADO THAT LASTED FROM ABOUT 435 TO 445 PM. ESTIMATED PATH WIDTH WAS 100 TO 150 YARDS WITH PEAK WINDS AROUND 90 TO 10 (FGF)
THIS TORNADO TRACKED FOR ABOUT 2.5 MILES FROM ABOUT 3.5 MILES NNE OF REYNOLDS ABOUT 6 MILES NE OF REYNOLDS BY 448 PM CDT. THE TORNADO SNAPPED SEVERAL COTTONWOOD AND ASH (FGF)
